abstract_ssm: Fay Chiang (1952-2017) was a poet, writer, visual artist, and activist. She was the director of Basement Workshop, an Asian American arts organization, and the author of numerous works spanning poetry, fiction, and non-fiction including In the City of Contradictions, Miwa's Song, and 7 Continents 9 Lives. In addition to her writings, Chiang also worked with numerous non-profit groups which combined cultural and educational work with community activism. The Fay Chiang Papers (1960-2017) consists of materials created and collected by Chiang documenting her writing career, involvement with various socio-political arts organizations including Basement Workshop, activism on behalf of Asian Americans, and some aspects of her personal life. Materials in this collection include photographs, personal correspondence, journals, notebooks, address books, project files for arts and community activism efforts, original drawings, administrative documents, and original writings in various formats and stages of completion. The collection also includes a small number of objects and video recordings.
